title: It's a scream! Halloween night partygoers brave the cold with some outrageous outfits in Newcastle, Leeds and Portsmouth
description: Thousands of people hit the bars and clubs on Tuesday night across the country as they prepared for an evening of Halloween hi-jinks.

title: Eighth Covid wave strikes Australia: Chief medical officer Paul Kelly reassures strain is less 'severe' than predecessors
description: The revelation comes less than two weeks after chief medical officer Professor Paul Kelly announced the end of the Covid emergency response on October 20.

title: Festive families to see double this Christmas as new trend for two trees per house is predicted
description: As reported in The Times, 40 per cent of homes with children and 30 per cent without will display a 'show tree,' along with their traditional evergreen.

title: Luxury bag brand created by designer who couldn't even read the alphabet at school because of crippling dyslexia becomes favourite with celebrities including Liv Bentley and Rachel Stevens
description: Natalie Dennis is taking the fashion world by storm with her elegant designer handbags, despite only leaving school with one GCSE. Her brand launched eight months ago and is in Harrods.

title: Michael Gove accuses big business of being 'woke just for show' to cover up worsening inequality in speech to the Alliance for Responsible Citizenship
description: Michael Gove has hit out at woke capitalism at a speech given to the centre-right Alliance for Responsible Citizenship (ARC) conference in London.

title: Time to batten down the hatches TODAY as monster Storm Ciaran arrives with 80mph gales as the Met issue amber warnings for the UK
description: The Met Office has issued both yellow and 'danger to life' amber warnings between today and Friday in anticipation of Storm Ciaran.

title: ABC announces major change to its breakfast show as host Lisa Millar disappears regularly to work on 'other projects'
description: The ABC has announced a major shake up of its News Breakfast television show, with a new newsreader and presenter joining the team from Monday, November 6.

title: Convicted terrorist Abdul Nacer Benbrika wins high-court bid to restore his Australian citizenship
description: The Australian citizenship of convicted terrorist Abdul Nacer Benbrika has been restored by the nation's highest court.

title: Mark Dreyfus's wife Deborah dies surrounded by her family
description: Attorney-General Mark Dreyfus's wife of 44 years has tragically died after a lengthy battle with illness.

title: CUNY adjunct professor is filmed ATTACKING onlookers who filmed her tearing down posters for kidnapped Israelis
description: An academic has gone viral after she attacked onlookers who filmed her tearing down posters for kidnapped Israelis who were taken hostage in the shock Hamas attacks.

title: Antiques dealer hauled into court accused of deceiving a pensioner couple he paid £130 to for an African mask - before he sold it on for £3.6million
description: Following the opening of the case today, the Gabonese government has asked for the legal proceedings to come to a halt pending a decision on its own complaint.

title: Messages furore is symptomatic of way slippery SNP handled the pandemic, writes EDDIE BARNES
description: Only with the SNP Government would we end up with an inquiry into an inquiry.

title: Now give menopausal NHS workers access to an open window, health chiefs told
description: NHS staff going through the ­menopause will be offered access to open windows and extended breaks in a bid to ease their symptoms.

title: All tricks and no treats in the great Holyrood Hallowe'en horror show, writes STEPHEN DAISLEY
description: A dark Hallowe'en afternoon was brooding over Holyrood when Shona Robison stood up.

title: Humiliated: SNP forced to hand over 14,000 Covid messages after legal threat
description: Humza Yousaf's government performed a humiliating U-turn after it was forced to hand over thousands of private messages to the UK Covid-19 public inquiry.

title: Hawthorn hit-and-run: Nine-year-old injured and driver arrested after fleeing the scene
description: A child has been injured following a hit-and-run crash after two cars collided that led to one of the vehicle's being flipped over on it's side.

title: Out of tune! Jersey Boys sing-a-long couple given court let off
description: Elizabeth Montague and Scott Kirk caused a disturbance that forced a performance of the Jersey Boys show at the Playhouse Theatre in Edinburgh to be halted.

title: Real estate market rocked after jury in landmark anti-trust case awards $1.8 billion to homeowners, saying realtors conspire to keep commissions on sales artificially high
description: A Missouri jury has handed down a landmark ruling against the National Association of Realtors and several large residential brokerages for artificially inflating commissions.

title: 'Hezbollah are better soldiers than Hamas - we could be next': RICHARD PENDLEBURY reports from one of the most strategically vulnerable communities in Israel
description: Uria Goldman discussed the 'situation' in Kibbutz Ma'yaan Baruch. He is armed with an assault rifle and patrols the otherwise deserted California-style neighbourhoods on a golf buggy.

title: Six in 10 teachers in schools rated 'good' or 'outstanding' by Ofsted believe their rating is wrong, survey finds
description: Commissioned by the Beyond Ofsted inquiry, the poll also found that 74 per cent described their experiences with the education watchdog as 'negative'.
